None.

## Hints for Future Agents
- <C-a> is NOT in telescope's default insert-mode mappings, so claiming it does
  not shadow a built-in telescope action. (Native Vim insert-mode <C-a> = repeat
  last inserted text; overridden only inside the telescope prompt.)
- insert_abspath_a_insert semantics (see plugin _insert_path, lua/
  telescope_insert_path/init.lua:100): location "a" => append after cursor,
  vim_mode "i" => after putting text it calls startinsert and advances the cursor,
  so you land back in INSERT mode in the buffer you launched the picker from. All
  actions call `stopinsert` first, so they work fine invoked from insert mode.
- The other six path mappings remain normal-mode-only; user may later ask to add
  insert-mode variants for those too.

## Codebase Discoveries
- path_actions has a metatable whose __index ERRORS on unknown keys (init.lua:6-10
  of the plugin). So any mistyped action name in the mappings would blow up
  telescope.setup at config load. A clean headless load therefore also doubles as
  validation that every mapped action name exists.

